      "\n  have h₁ : (l.set idx (l1.eraseIdx idx1)).flatten = (l.set idx l1).flatten.eraseIdx (List快来点: ℕ) := by sorry\n  have h₂ : l1[idx1] = (l.set idx l1).flatten[idx''] := by sorry\n  obtain ⟨ih,⟩ :=  $by sorry\n  use ih\n  <;> simp_all\n  <;> try aesop\n  <;> try linarith",
      "computing the sum of lengths of the first `idx` lists. \n\nWait, let's think differently:\n\nAssume `l = prefix ++ [current] ++ suffix`, where `current` is the list at index `idx`, and similarly for `l1`.\n\nThen `(l.set idx l1)` is `prefix ++ [l1] ++ suffix`.\n\nThe `flatten` is `prefixFlatten ++ l1 ++ suffixFlatten`.\n\nNow, `(l1.eraseIdx idx1)` is `l1` minus its `idx1`-th element.\n\nSo, `(l.set idx (l1.eraseIdx idx1)).flatten` is `prefixFlatten ++ (l1.eraseIdx idx1) ++ suffixFlatten`.\n\nBut `prefixFlatten ++ l1 ++ suffixFlatten` can have `l1[idx1]` erased at position `prefixFlatten.length + idx1`, because `l1[idx1]` is the `(prefixFlatten.length + idx1)`-th element of the full flattened list.\n\n#### Finding `idx'`\n\nIn other words, `idx' = (length of prefixFlatten) + idx1`, because:\n`(l.set idx l1).flatten = prefixFlatten ++ l1 ++ suffixFlatten`, and thus, its `(length of prefixFlatten + idx1)`-th element is `l1[idx1]`.\n\nThus, erasing it gives `prefixFlatten ++ (l1.eraseIdx idx1) ++ suffixFlatten = (l.set idx (l1.eraseIdx idx1)).flatten`.\n\nNow, to find `length of prefixFlatten`, observe that it is the sum of lengths of the first `idx` lists in `l` (i.e., the prefix).\n\nAlternatively, in Lean, we can proceed as follows:\n\n1. Compute `pre_len` as the sum of lengths of `l.take idx`.\n2. Then in `(l.set idx l1).flatten`, the element `l1[idx1]` is found at `pre_len + idx1`, provided that:\n   - `pre_len + idx1 < (l",
      "\n  have h₁ : ∃ (i : Nat), i < (l.set idx l1).flatten.length := by\n    have h₂ : 0 < (l.set idx l1).flatten.length := by\n      have h₃ : 0 < l1.length := by\n        have h₄ : idx1 < l1.length := hidx1\n        omega\n      have h₄ : (l.set idx l1).length > 0 := by\n        have h₅ : l.length > 0 := by\n          have h₆ : idx < l.length := hidx\n          omega\n        have h₆ : (l.set idx l1).length = l.length := by\n          simp [List.length_set]\n        omega\n      have h₅ : (l.set idx l1).flatten.length > 0 := by\n        have h₆ : ∀ (l : List (List α)), l.length > 0 → l.flatten.length > 0 := by\n          intro l hl\n          induction' l with hd tl ih\n          · simp_all\n          · cases hd with\n            | nil => simp_all [List.length]\n            | cons a tl => simp_all [List.length]\n        exact h₆ (l.set idx l1) (by omega)\n      omega\n    omega\n  have h₂ : ∃ (i : Fin (l.set idx l1).flatten.length), (l1)[idx1] = (l.set idx l1).flatten[i] := by\n    have h₃ : ∃ (i : Fin (l.set idx l1).flatten.length), (l1)[idx1] = (l.set idx l1).flatten[i] := by\n      have h₄ : (l1)[idx1] ∈ (l.set idx l1).flatten := by\n        have h₅ : (l1)[idx1] ∈ l1 := by\n          apply List.get_mem\n        have h₆ : l1 ∈ (l.set idx l1) := by\n          have h₇ : l1 = (l.set idx l1)[idx] := by\n            simp [List.set]\n            <;>\n            (try omega) <;>\n            (try simp_all [List.get]) <;>\n            (try aesop)\n          have h₈ : (l.set idx l1)[idx] ∈ (l.set idx l1) := by\n            apply List.get_mem\n          simp_all [h₇]\n        have h₇ : (l1)[idx1] ∈ (l.insertNth (l1)[idx1] (l1)).flatten := by\n          simp_all [List.insertNth, List.mem_flatten]\n          <;>\n          (try aesop) <;>\n          (try omega)\n        have h₈ : (l.set idx l1) = l.insertNth l1 idx := by\n          simp [List.set, List.insertNth]\n          <;>\n          (try omega) <;>\n          (try aesop)\n        have h₉ : (l1)[idx1] ∈ (l.set idx l1).flatten := by\n          rw [h₈]\n          simp_all [List.mem_flatten]\n          <;>\n          (try aesop) <;>\n          (try omega)\n        exact h₉\n      have h₅ : ∃ (i : Fin (l.set idx l1).flatten.length), (l1)[idx1] = (l.set idx l1).flatten[i] := by\n        have h₆ : (l1)[idx1] ∈ (l.set idx l1).flatten := h₄\n        have h₇ : ∃ (i : Fin (l.set idx l1).flatten.length), (l.set idx l1).flatten[i] = (l1)[idx1] := by\n          classical\n            have h₈ : ∃ (i : Fin (l.set idx l1).flatten.length), (l.set idx l1).flatten[i] = (l1)[idx1] := by\n              simpa [List.mem_iff_get] using h₆\n            exact h₈\n        obtain ⟨i, hi⟩ := h₇\n        refine' ⟨i, _⟩\n        simp_all\n        <;>\n        (try omega) <;>\n        (try aesop)\n      exact h₅\n    exact h₃\n  obtain ⟨i, hi⟩ := h₂\n  have h₃ : (l.set idx (l1.eraseIdx idx1)).flatten = (l.set idx l1).flatten.eraseIdx i := by\n    have h₄ : (l.set idx (l1.eraseIdx idx1)).flatten = (l.set idx l1).flatten.eraseIdx i := by\n      have h₅ : (l1.eraseIdx idx1).length ≤ l1.length := by\n        have h₆ : l1.eraseIdx idx1 ≤ l1 := by\n          apply List.subset_iff.mpr\n          intro x hx\n          by_contra h\n          simp_all [List.mem_eraseAll]\n          <;>\n          (try omega) <;>\n          (try aesop)\n        have h₆ : (l1.eraseIdx idx1).length ≤ l1.length := by\n          apply List.length_le_of_subset h₆\n        exact h₆\n      have h₆ : (l.set idx (l1.eraseIdx idx1)).flatten = (l.set idx l1).flatten.eraseIdx i := by\n        have h₇ : (l.set idx (l1.eraseIdx idx1)).flatten = (l.set idx l1).flatten.eraseIdx i := by\n          simp [List.set, List.erase, List.eraseIdx, List.eraseAt, List.get] at hi ⊢\n          <;>\n          (try omega) <;>\n          (try aesop)\n          <;>\n          (try\n            {\n              simp_all [List.length]\n              <;>\n              (try omega) <;>\n              (try aesop)\n            })\n          <;>\n          (try\n            {